\fi-360\li720\b There are lots of changes. I'd read this list and look out for new bugs.\b0\par
{\pntext\f0 2.\tab}Added splash screen and updated parser loading process to be more responsive.\par
{\pntext\f0 3.\tab}Added status indicator to the Manage Characters table in Trigger Manager. Red indiciates the file has not been opened yet. The warning/orange color means that the file is open but no recent activity (2 mins). Green means the file is active and busy.\par
{\pntext\f0 4.\tab}Updated Log Readers to better handle unreliable files or shared via network.\par
{\pntext\f0 5.\tab}Updated EQLP:STOP command to attempt to stop sounds.\par
{\pntext\f0 6.\tab}Updated Log Management to better handle multiple files being archievd at once. I think this was causing multiple archives to sometimes happen of the same file. Also, updated the UI to prevent enabled file age and sizes to both be set to any value.\par
{\pntext\f0 7.\tab}Updated installer to link to latest .Net 8.0.5 and to cleanup old log files.\par
{\pntext\f0 8.\tab}Fix for Timer Bars not updating with specified Font Family. \b You may want to switch to Segoe UI or Roboto in your Timer Overlays if they look different than they used to.\b0\par
{\pntext\f0 9.\tab}Fix for default (Trigger Time) Timer sorting.\par
{\pntext\f0 10.\tab}Fix for parser not displaying after windows resolution is lowered.\par
{\pntext\f0 11.\tab}Fix for crash that could occur when changing log files when no data is loaded.\par
{\pntext\f0 12.\tab}Fix for Pet/Players list not updating its counts correctly when changing log files.\par
{\pntext\f0 13.\tab}Fix for server name not being parsed correctly from archived files which lead to the Pet list not being displayed for the server.\par

